\h Obadiah
\toc1 Obadiah
\toc2 Obadiah
\mt1 Obadiah
\c 1
\p
\v 1 The vision of Obadiah.
\s1 Edom Will Be Humbled
\q1 Thus says the Lord \nd God\nd* \x + \xo 1:1 \xt See Jer. 49:7-22; Ezek. 25:12-14 \x*concerning Edom:
\q1 \x + \xo 1:1 \xt For ver. 1-4, see Jer. 49:14-16\x*We have heard a report from the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and a messenger has been sent among the nations:
\q1 “Rise up! Let us rise against her for battle!”
\q1
\v 2 Behold, I will make you small among the nations;
\q2 you shall be utterly despised.\f + \fr 2 \ft Or \fq Behold, I have made you small among the nations; you are utterly despised\f*
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Num. 24:21, 22] \x*The pride of your heart has deceived you,
\q2 you who live in the clefts of the rock,\f + \fr 3 \ft Or \+tl Sela\+tl*\f*
\q2 in your lofty dwelling,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Isa. 14:13-15]\x*who say in your heart,
\q2 “Who will bring me down to the ground?”
\q1
\v 4 Though you soar aloft like the eagle,
\q2 though your nest is set among the stars,
\q2 from there I will bring you down,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 5 If \x + \xo 1:5 \xt Jer. 49:9\x*thieves came to you,
\q2 if plunderers came by night—
\q2 how you have been destroyed!—
\q2 would they not steal only enough for themselves?
\q1 If \x + \xo 1:5 \xt Jer. 49:9\x*grape gatherers came to you,
\q2 would they not leave gleanings?
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 1:6 \xt [Jer. 49:10]\x*How Esau has been pillaged,
\q2 his treasures sought out!
\q1
\v 7 All your allies have driven you to your border;
\q2 those at peace with you have deceived you;
\q1 they have prevailed against you;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:7 \xt [Ps. 41:9] \x*those who eat your bread\f + \fr 7 \ft Hebrew lacks \fq those who eat\f* have set a trap beneath you—
\q2 \x + \xo 1:7 \xt [Jer. 49:7]\x*you have\f + \fr 7 \ft Hebrew \fq he has\f* no understanding.
\b
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 1:8 \xt [Isa. 29:14] \x*Will I not on that day, declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 destroy the wise men out of Edom,
\q2 and understanding out of \x + \xo 1:8 \xt [Ezek. 35:2]\x*Mount Esau?
\q1
\v 9 And your mighty men shall be dismayed, \x + \xo 1:9 \xt Amos 1:12; See 1 Chr. 1:45 \x*O Teman,
\q2 so that every man from \x + \xo 1:9 \xt [See ver. 8 above]\x*Mount Esau will be cut off by slaughter.
\s1 Edom’s Violence Against Jacob
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 1:10 \xt Num. 20:20, 21 \x*Because of the violence done to your brother Jacob,
\q2 shame shall cover you,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:10 \xt [Ezek. 35:9]\x*and you shall be cut off forever.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt Ps. 137:7; [Jer. 12:14] \x*On the day that you stood aloof,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt See 2 Kgs. 25:10-20 \x*on the day that strangers carried off his wealth
\q1 and foreigners entered his gates
\q2 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt Joel 3:3\x*and cast lots for Jerusalem,
\q2 you were like one of them.
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 1:12 \xt [Ps. 22:17] \x*But do not gloat over the day of your brother
\q2 in the day of his misfortune;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:12 \xt [Mic. 4:11; 7:8] \x*do not rejoice over the people of Judah
\q2 in the day of their ruin;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:12 \xt [1 Sam. 2:3]\x*do not boast\f + \fr 12 \ft Hebrew \fq do not enlarge your mouth\f*
\q2 in the day of distress.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [Prov. 17:5] \x*Do not enter the gate of my people
\q2 in the day of their calamity;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [Prov. 17:5] \x*do not gloat over his disaster
\q2 in the day of his calamity;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [Ezek. 35:10]\x*do not loot his wealth
\q2 in the day of his calamity.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [Ezek. 21:21]\x*Do not stand at the crossroads
\q2 to cut off his fugitives;
\q1 do not hand over his survivors
\q2 in the day of distress.
\s1 The Day of the \nd Lord\nd* Is Near
\q1
\v 15 For \x + \xo 1:15 \xt See Joel 1:15 \x*the day of the \nd Lord\nd* is near upon all the nations.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:15 \xt Jer. 50:29; Ezek. 35:15; Hab. 2:8\x*As you have done, it shall be done to you;
\q2 your deeds shall return on your own head.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 1:16 \xt See Jer. 25:27, 28 \x*For as you have drunk on \x + \xo 1:16 \xt See Joel 3:17\x*my holy mountain,
\q2 so all the nations shall drink continually;
\q1 they shall drink and swallow,
\q2 and shall be as though they had never been.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 1:17 \xt [Amos 9:8]; See Joel 2:32 \x*But in Mount Zion there shall be those who escape,
\q2 and it shall be holy,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:17 \xt [Amos 9:12]\x*and the house of Jacob shall possess their own possessions.
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 1:18 \xt Zech. 12:6; [Isa. 10:17; Jer. 5:14] \x*The house of Jacob shall be a fire,
\q2 and the house of Joseph a flame,
\q2 and the house of Esau \x + \xo 1:18 \xt See Joel 2:5 \x*stubble;
\q1 they shall burn them and consume them,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:18 \xt Ezek. 25:14\x*and there shall be no survivor for the house of Esau,
\qr for the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken.
\s1 The Kingdom of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q1
\v 19 Those of \x + \xo 1:19 \xt [Josh. 10:40; Judg. 1:9] \x*the Negeb \x + \xo 1:19 \xt [See ver. 17 above] \x*shall possess \x + \xo 1:19 \xt ver. 8 \x*Mount Esau,
\q2 and those of the Shephelah shall possess \x + \xo 1:19 \xt Jer. 17:26 \x*the land of the Philistines;
\q1 they shall possess the land of Ephraim and the land of \x + \xo 1:19 \xt See Jer. 23:13\x*Samaria,
\q2 and Benjamin shall possess Gilead.
\q1
\v 20 The exiles of this host of the people of Israel
\q2 shall possess the land of the Canaanites as far as \x + \xo 1:20 \xt 1 Kgs. 17:9; [Luke 4:26]\x*Zarephath,
\q1 and the exiles of Jerusalem who are in Sepharad
\q2 shall possess the cities of the Negeb.
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 1:21 \xt [2 Kgs. 13:5; Isa. 19:20; 1 Tim. 4:16; James 5:20] \x*Saviors shall go up to Mount Zion
\q2 to rule \x + \xo 1:21 \xt [See ver. 19 above] \x*Mount Esau,
\q2 and \x + \xo 1:21 \xt Ps. 22:28; Dan. 2:44; 7:14, 27; Zech. 14:9; Luke 1:33; 1 Cor. 15:24; Rev. 11:15; 19:6\x*the kingdom shall be the \nd Lord\nd*’s.
